							 What is The Young Scientist Program? 
							 The Young Scientist Program is designed to attract high school students into scientific careers through activities emphasizing hands-on research and individualized contact between young people and active scientists.
							 
							  Continue Reading È  
						 
					 
					 
						
						 
							 Graduate Student Volunteers are at the core of YSP 
							 As students and scientists, it is our hope that sharing our enthusiasm for what we do will encourage younger individuals to also pursue careers in science.
							 
							  Continue Reading È  
						 
					 
					 
						
						 
							 The Student Experience 
							 YSP students gain hands on experience from experts in their field and an appreciation for science. 
														 
							  Continue Reading È  
						 
					 
					 
						
						 
							 The Teacher Experience 
							 YSP provides teachers with laboratory experience through an 8-week independent summer research project with a volunteer in a Washington University laboratory. 
							 
							  Learn More È  
						 
					 
					 
						
						 
							 Latest YSP News & Events 
							 The Young Scientist Program has a dynamic program of events year round - keep up to date by visiting our blog!
							 
